{"id":"261714414_Discrete_Lorentz_covariance_for_Quantum_Walks_and_Quantum_Cellular_Automata","abstract":"We formalize a notion of discrete Lorentz transforms for Quantum Walks (QW)\nand Quantum Cellular Automata (QCA), in (1 + 1)-dimensional discrete spacetime.\nThe theory admits a diagrammatic representation in terms of a few local,\ncircuit equivalence rules. Within this framework, we show the first-order-only\ncovariance of the Dirac QW. We then introduce the Clock QW and the Clock QCA,\nand prove that they are exactly discrete Lorentz covariant. The theory also\nallows for non-homogeneous Lorentz transforms, between non-inertial frames.","authors":["Pablo Arrighi","Stefano Facchini","Marcelo Forets"],"meta":["April 2014New Journal of Physics 16(9)","DOI:10.1088/1367-2630/16/9/093007","SourcearXiv"],"references":["258941370_Quantum_frames_of_reference","258052347_Doubly-Special_Relativity_from_Quantum_Cellular_Automata","249012022_The_Dirac_equation_as_a_quantum_walk_Higher_dimensions_observational_convergence","319774715_The_Dirac_Equation","263793615_QUANTUM_GRAVITY_PHENOMENOLOGY_LORENTZ_INVARIANCE_AND_DISCRETENESS","259220361_Discrete_Spacetime_and_Relativistic_Quantum_Particles","259151178_Action_principle_for_cellular_automata_and_the_linearity_of_quantum_mechanics","257201485_Decoupled_Quantum_Walks_models_of_the_Klein-Gordon_and_wave_equations","256762556_Quantum_Walks_in_artificial_electric_and_gravitational_Fields","248778218_Discrete_Space-Time_and_Integral_Lorentz_Transformations","243486624_An_Introduction_to_Relativistic_Quantum_Fied_Theory","237082442_Derivation_of_the_Dirac_Equation_from_Principles_of_Information_Processing","236597389_The_Dirac_Quantum_Cellular_Automaton_in_one_dimension_Zitterbewegung_and_scattering_from_potential","236545475_The_Dirac_Equation","234969258_Relativistic_effects_and_rigorous_limits_for_discrete-_and_continuous-time_quantum_walks"]}